      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FERAGO (1) is a talented jumper who has been in excellent form of late. Saluted at Warrnambool two runs back then again got the job done last time at Casterton, winning with 4 lengths in hand. In-form jumper who is a great chance to score again. FLASHLIGHT (3) was well in commission and turned in a nice effort last time out when he scored on his jumps debut in a hurdle at Casterton. Can only be better for that and looks the biggest danger to FERAGO. SPLIT (4) was very good when returning from a 228-day layoff most recently, finishing 6 lengths back in third on the flat at Casterton over 2000m. That run was the first for the Patrick Payne stable. Will come on from that run and is worth considering. GAMBU (2) backs up just seven days after finishing fourth in a hurdle at Hamilton, but beaten 22 lengths. That was on the back of a solid third in a 2050m flat race two starts back. Expecting more this time. FLYING WITNESS (5) has talent but hasn't shown a lot of late.",
